IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE MEDICAL AND DENTAL PRIMARY CARE SERVICES TO A MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED POPULATION.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO PROVIDE ACCESSIBLE, QUALITY PRIMARY AND RELATED HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO MILWAUKEE RESIDENTS, WITH OUR CONTINUING EMPHASIS ON MEDICALLY-UNDERSERVED FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS.
IRS990.Desc: TO PROVIDE ACCESSIBLE, QUALITY PRIMARY AND RELATED HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO MILWAUKEE RESIDENTS, WITH OUR CONTINUING EMPHASIS ON MEDICALLY-UNDERSERVED FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS. 14,136 PATIENTS WERE SERVED DURING THE YEAR (RESULTING IN 46,286 ENCOUNTERS).IN NOVEMBER, 2022 MILWAUKEE COUNTY BEHAVIORAL HEALTH DEPARTMENT STARTED TO LEASE SPACE FROM MHSI ISSAC COGGS CLINIC AT 8200 W. SILVER SPRING DRIVE IN MILWAUKEE IN ORDER TO PROVIDE BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CRISIS MANAGEMENT TO THE COMMUNITY. THE SPACE WAS RENOVATED WITH FUNDS FROM THE MILWAUKEE PARTNERSHIP CAMPAIGN AND MILWAUKEE COUNTY. THE LEASED SPACE IS 1,791 SQUARE FEET. THE COST IS $5,626.25 PER MONTH WITH AN ANNUAL INCREASE OF 3% ON A 5 YEAR TERM.

OtherLiabilitiesOrgGrp.Desc: AMOUNTS PAYABLE UNDER FISCAL AGENT RESPONSIBILITIES

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZES THE BENEFIT OF A TAX POSITION ONLY AFTER DETERMINING WHETHER IT IS MORE LIKELY THAN NOT THAT THE TAXING AUTHORITY WOULD SUSTAIN THE TAX POSITION UPON EXAMINATION OF THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE TAX POSITION ASSUMING THE TAXING AUTHORITY HAS FULL KNOWLEDGE OF ALL INFORMATION. THE ORGANIZATION HAS RECORDED NO ASSETS OR LIABILITIES RELATED TO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.

THE ORGANIZATION DOCUMENTS ALL RELEVANT INFORMATION PERTAINING TO MEDICAL ASSISTANCE GIVEN TO THE PATIENT, IN THE PATIENT RECORDS. ASSISTANCE WITH TRANSPORTATION IS PROVIDED THROUGH BUS VOUCHERS. THE PATIENT SIGNS FOR THE RECEIPT OF THE BUS VOUCHER AND A RECORD IS MAINTAINED IN THE EIP DEPARTMENT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE CONTROLLER, CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER, AND PRESIDENT/CEO OF THE ORGANIZATION. AFTER SATISFACTORY REVIEW, IT IS PRESENTED TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE FOR REVIEW. BEFORE FILING WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE, THE FORM 990 IS MADE AVAILABLE TO ALL MEMBERS OF THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION REQUIRES THAT ALL EMPLOYEES AND BOARD MEMBERS DISCLOSE IN WRITING AND UPDATE AT LEAST ANNUALLY, ALL BUSINESS AND IMMEDIATE FAMILY RELATIONSHIPS WHICH MIGHT POTENTIALLY CREATE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST. IN ADDITION, EMPLOYEES WITH NON-COMPETE CONTRACTS MUST DISCLOSE TO THE PRESIDENT/CEO, AND PRESIDENT/CEO MUST DISCLOSE TO THE BOARD CHAIRPERSON, IN WRITING THE SPECIFICS OF ANY PLAN TO ACCEPT OUTSIDE EMPLOYMENT SO THAT OUTSIDE EMPLOYMENT MAY BE DETERMINED IF POTENTIAL CONFLICT EXISTS. NO BOARD MEMBER MAY VOTE ON ANY MATTER WHICH MAY DIRECTLY OR INDIRECTLY RESULT IN FINANCIAL GAIN TO THAT MEMBER, OR WHICH MAY CONFLICT WITH THAT MEMBER'S OBLIGATIONS TO ANOTHER ORGANIZATION'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS. PROVIDED THAT THE BOARD MEMBER HAS FIRST DISCLOSED A CONFLICT OR POTENTIAL CONFLICT, AND ABSTAINS FROM VOTING IN THAT REGARD, HE/SHE MAY PARTICIPATE IN DISCUSSIONS RELATING TO THAT MATTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PROCESS FOR DETERMINING THE EXECUTIVE COMPENSATIONS IS BASED ON PERFORMANCE EVALUATION, ANALYZING COMPENSATION SURVEYS/STUDIES, REVIEW OF 990S OF OTHER ORGANIZATIONS AND APPROVAL OF THE REVISED EMPLOYMENT AGREEMENT BY THE BOARD CHAIR.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
